# E-commerce Sales Analysis Project

## Project Overview

This project was completed as part of my internship program at Decode Labs. The objective was to analyze business data, improve data quality, identify trends, and generate actionable business insights through data analysis and visualization.

## Tools Used

* Microsoft Excel
* SQL
* Power BI
* GitHub

## Project Workflow

### 1. Data Cleaning (Excel)

* Handled 309 missing values in the Coupon Code column.
* Checked for duplicates and data inconsistencies.
* Validated data quality and prepared the dataset for analysis.
* Performed outlier detection on sales data.

### 2. Descriptive Analysis (Excel)

* Identified the most purchased products.
* Analyzed the most used coupon codes.
* Identified the most effective referral sources.
* Examined payment method usage.
* Evaluated order status distribution.

### 3. Trend Analysis (Excel)

* Analyzed the top-selling products across 2023–2025.
* Investigated sales trends over time.
* Compared referral sources against product purchases.
* Measured yearly sales performance and decline patterns.

### 4. Business Analysis (SQL)

* Analyzed revenue by order status.
* Evaluated product revenue performance over time.
* Classified orders into Successful and Unsuccessful categories.
* Calculated revenue percentages for successful and unsuccessful orders.
* Identified products contributing to revenue leakage.

### 5. Dashboard Development (Power BI)

Created an interactive dashboard consisting of:

* Revenue & Sales Performance Analysis
* Customer Behavior & Marketing Analysis
* Product & Order Analysis

## Key Findings

* Revenue declined consistently between 2023 and 2025.
* Chair, Laptop, and Printer were the most purchased products.
* Chair experienced the sharpest decline in performance.
* Only 38.64% of revenue came from successful orders.
* 61.36% of revenue was associated with pending, returned, or cancelled orders.
* Chair products generated the highest unsuccessful revenue.
* Email, Google Ads, Facebook, and Instagram were the leading referral sources.

## Business Recommendations

* Investigate factors contributing to high cancellation and return rates.
* Focus marketing efforts on high-performing referral channels.
* Review operational issues affecting Chair product sales.
* Monitor declining revenue trends and customer purchasing behavior.

